Ambassador Princeton Lyman has served as President Obama's Special Envoy to Sudan and South Sudan for the past two years. He has played a crucial role in helping South Sudan become independent and fostering peace between Sudan and South Sudan. The President commends Lyman for his dedicated service and acknowledges the positive impact he has had on the people of Sudan and South Sudan. The President expresses gratitude for Lyman's leadership and wishes him and his family well in their future endeavors.